{
  "_doc": "Phase-5a demo: IMM (constant injector) and PC (program counter) — the first two CPU components reach Verilog. Click VERILOG to see how each lowers:\n  • IMM — pure combinational. One `assign net = 8'h2a;` line and that's it. No clock, no state.\n  • PC — clocked register, structurally a COUNTER cousin. Priority chain: CLR > JUMP > EN > hold. JUMP loads the absolute address from JUMP_ADDR; EN increments by 1; CLR resets to 0.\nA pcRelative variant exists too — when set on the node, the JUMP branch becomes `pc + 1 + offset` (the canonical PC-relative branch), but this demo shows the simpler absolute-jump form.",
